# Vercel builds ONLY apps/web (+ packages/* workspace). The GitHub deploy sees just
# git-tracked files; the CLI otherwise uploads the whole tree (Python .venv, spikes,
# model caches → 1.9 GB, over the 100 MB/file limit). Exclude everything the frontend
# build doesn't need. Media patterns are ROOT-anchored so apps/web/public assets stay.
services/
deploy/
design-md/
docs/
**/.venv/
.claude/
.playwright-mcp/
*.mp4
*.mov
# ...but DO ship the landing hero demo video. `*.mp4` above is UNanchored (unlike `/*.jpg`), so it
# would 404 the public demo clip; negate exactly that one file (heavy test mp4s under services/ stay out).
!apps/web/public/demo/pipeline-demo.mp4
/*.png
/*.jpeg
/*.jpg
/runs.jsonl
/.git-commit-*.txt
/.commit-msg
/package-lock.json
/icon.png
